PART I.芒聙聰

Harbor Fees

SEC 2. The following schedule of fees for each entrance to or departure from a port of entry in the Philippines hereby established:

For each entrance from a foreign port P50.00;

For each departure to a foreign port 50.00;

For each coastwise entrance or departure:

In case of vessel from 6 to 15 tons net

In case of vessel more than 15 but not more than 75 tons net

In case of vessel more than 75 but not more than 150 tons net

In case of vessel more than 150 but not more than 200 tons net

In case of vessel more than 200 but not more than 250 tons net

In case of vessel more than 250 but not more than 300 tons net

In case of vessel more than 300 but not more than 400 tons net

In case of vessel more than 400 tons net

1.00;

2.00;

4.00;

6.00;

10.00;

12.00;

16.00;

20.00;

Provided,

That the following are exempt from the payment of such fees:

Vessels entering the port for the sole purpose of receiving bunker fuel and/or ship supplies or changing pilots, and remaining less than twenty-four hours in the port;

Vessels passing through the port and remaining less than twelve hours and not receiving or discharging cargo;

Vessels passing through the port and remaining less than twelve hours and not receiving or discharging cargo;

Vessels owned by the Philippine Government on any foreign government not engaged in carrying cargo, or passengers for hire; and

Private, non-commercial pleasure craft.
